Two types of DOM interactions:
- Manipulating elements around (cloning, hiding, showing)
- Retrieving data from the DOM and inserting data into the DOM

Manipulating elements
-----------------------
Examples: creating another form row, hiding initial form, showing results page

Retrieving elements
-----------------------
- First create a function that triggers from an event (such as clicking a button)
  - This function will read the form, taking the data from each input and storing it in the data structure

- The other part is a function that retrieves data from the structure, and fills the DOM
  - This function reads data from the data structure and inserts it into the DOM


Creating two pages out of one
--------------------------------

HTML

<body>
  <div class="main1"></div>
  <div class="main2"></div>
</body>

CSS

.main1 {}
.main2 { display: none; }

JS

$('.main1').hide();
$('.main2').show();
